<title>BULGARIA: Bulgaria offers 4.8 bln levs 98-day T-bills Oct 25.</title>
<headline>Bulgaria offers 4.8 bln levs 98-day T-bills Oct 25.</headline>
<dateline>SOFIA 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bulgaria's Finance Ministry will offer 4.8 billion levs of 98-day floater coupon T-bills at an auction on Friday, the Bulgarian National Bank (BNB) said.</p>
<p>The issue will be offered with no minimum acceptable price set in advance by the ministry.</p>
<p>The coupon was set equal to the BNB's central interest rate (CIR) for the period to maturity. The CIR is now set at 20 percent monthly or 240 percent annually.</p>
<p>Details of the issue follow:</p>
<p> Issue number	 BG 3019996027</p>
<p> Par value	    4.8 bln levs</p>
<p> Auction date	 October 25, 1996</p>
<p> Issue date	   October 31, 1996</p>
<p> Maturity date	February 6, 1997</p>
<p>-- Sofia Newsroom, (++359-2) 981 8569</p>
